{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">crypto.library.ciphers()\n</pre><ul><li>Fetches the list of supported or built-in OpenSSL encryption ciphers, returning details about them as a string.</li></ul><h3><br></h3><h3>Returns</h3><ul><li>A string containing the list and details of the supported OpenSSL ciphers. <em><u>(string)</u></em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">local X = crypto.library.ciphers()\n</pre><ul><li>This retrieves the available ciphers and assigns the result to the variable <code>X</code>.</li></ul><h4><br></h4><h3>Warning</h3><ul><li>The return format is subject to change. This function is intended for interactive querying and debugging, not for use in production code relying on a fixed format.</li></ul>",
    "Name": "crypto.library.ciphers",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Returns the list of supported OpenSSL encryption ciphers."
}